r of Claude Code at Anthropic, joins Sequoia partner Lauren Reeder at AI Ascent 2026 to talk about where coding goes from here. He explains why he hasn't written a line of code in 2026, why he now ships dozens of PRs a day from his phone, and why he believes coding is effectively solved — at least for the code he writes. Also: why loops are the future, why he thinks Claude Code itself may be 100 lines of code a year from now, and why the invention of the printing press is the right analogy for what's about to happen to software.\n\n00:00 Introduction\n00:55 Claude Code Crowd Check\n02:39 Origin Story of Claude Code\n03:35 From Typeahead to Agents\n05:07 Is Coding Solved\n06:50 Boris Personal Workflow\n08:51 Future Teams and Generalists\n10:26 SaaS Apocalypse Predictions\n12:57 Audience Q\u0026A Deep Dive\n23:35 Closing and Whats Next","commandRuns":[{"startIndex":556,"length":5,"onTap":{"innertubeCommand":{"clickTrackingParams":"CBQQ040EGAciEwjgvOaJx7CUAxVBbfUHHeCjFCPKAQTsgh-N","commandMetadata":{"webCommandMetadata":{"url":"/watch?v=SlGRN8jh2RI","webPageType":"WEB_PAGE_TYPE_WATCH","rootVe":3832}},"watchEndpoint":{"videoId":"SlGRN8jh2RI","continuePlayback":true,"startTimeSeconds":0,"watchEndpointSupportedOnesieConfig":{"html5PlaybackOnesieConfig":{"commonConfig":{"url":"https://rr1---sn-un57sn7y.googlevideo.com/initplayback?source=youtube\u0026oeis=1\u0026c=WEB\u0026oad=3200\u0026ovd=3200\u0026oaad=11000\u0026oavd=11000\u0026ocs=700\u0026oewis=1\u0026oputc=1\u0026ofpcc=1\u0026msp=1\u0026odepv=1\u0026id=4a519137c8e1d912\u0026ip=94.156.205.128\u0026initcwndbps=2532500\u0026mt=1778478548\u0026oweuc="}}}}}},"onTapOptions":{"accessibilityInfo":{"accessibilityLabel":"0 秒"}}},{"startIndex":575,"length":5,"onTap":{"innertubeCommand":{"clickTrackingParams":"CBQQ040EGAciEwjgvOaJx7CUAxVBbfUHHeCjFCPKAQTsgh-N","commandMetadata":{"webCommandMetadata":{"url":"/watch?v=SlGRN8jh2RI\u0026t=55s","webPageType":"WEB_PAGE_TYPE_WATCH","rootVe":3832}},"watchEndpoint":{"videoId":"SlGRN8jh2R